column21:
@jwiggins

I wouldn't worry too much about it.

Thanks! I won't, then. :-)

PyPI upload is in progress...

Well, it was, until I discovered that since PEP 527, only one source distribution format can be uploaded to PyPI. That leaves us choosing between .tar.gz and .zip, and we should probably be consistent with our choices across all ETS packages.
@corranwebster, @jwiggins: Any strong opinions about whether we should upload .zip or .tar.gz?

Yes, that's a good point. When use_damaged_region is true, you will still encounter the problem addressed by this PR.
However I'm starting to think that we should maybe just remove this code altogether. You are likely right that it's a work in progress. Grepping the code for both chaco and enable leads me to believe that use_damaged_region is always false (unless user code explicitly sets it to true).
@rkern Do you remember the provenance of this feature? Should we keep the traits for backwards compatibility and remove all the code in methods which references them? (use_damaged_region and _update_region)

